view.name: Housing Maintenance Code Violations
view.attribution: Department of Housing Preservation and Development (HPD)
view.description:
Pursuant to New York Cityâ€™s Housing Maintenance Code, the Department of Housing 
Preservation and Development (HPD) issues violations against conditions in rental 
dwelling units that have been verified to violate the New York City Housing 
Maintenance Code (HMC) or the New York State Multiple Dwelling Law (MDL). 
Violations are issued when an inspection verifies that a violation of the HMC or MDL 
exists. It is closed when the violation is corrected, as observed/verified by HPD or as 
certified by the landlord.

columns.name: RegistrationID
columns.description: Unique identifier of valid registration information

columns.name: Boro
columns.description: Boro code (1 = Manhattan, 2 = Bronx, 3 = Brooklyn, 4 = Queens, 5 = Staten Island)

columns.name: Class
columns.description: Indicator of seriousness of the violations, where A is the least serious and C is the most serious

columns.name: InspectionDate
columns.description: Date when the violation was observed

columns.name: OriginalCertifyByDate
columns.description: Original date by when the owner was to inform HPD that the violation as corrected

columns.name: OriginalCorrectByDate
columns.description: Original date by when the owner was to correct the violation

columns.name: NewCertifyByDate
columns.description: Modified date by when the owner was to inform HPD that the violation as corrected

columns.name: NewCorrectByDate
columns.description: Modified date by when the owner was to correct the violation

columns.name: CertifiedDate
columns.description: Date when the violation was certified (if it was)

columns.name: OrderNumber
columns.description: Reference to the abstract description of the violation condition which cites a specific section of the law which is in violation

columns.name: NOVID
columns.description: Unique identifier of the Notice of Violation sent to the owner
